baby shower ideas for adopted baby when the baby has already been brought home my aunt has been trying to adopt a baby for years now and finally she got to bring her son home from guatemala about a month ago now we're throwing her a baby shower but what kind of fun shower things can we do considering she's not pregnant and the baby is already here and months old at that normally it's like guess how big her belly is games or something which we obviously can't do haha my son was the star of my baby shower my mother threw my shower after i welcomed my son home so i must admit there wasn't much time for games everyone wanted to hold my son but i have been to baby showers for adoptive families and i recommend the clothespin game that someone mentioned above another one is baby bingo where you give everyone a blank bingo card and ask them to fill in words of items that they expect the mother to receive i e diapers in one block onesie in another etc as she opens the gifts if you have the item on your list you cross it off the first one to reach bingo wins good luck and have fun EastEnders Game show Bingo Poker jargon Pyramid (game show) Wheel of Fortune Winning Streak Care Bears Childbirth Knots Landing Humphrey Bogart Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Infant Dominoes Rugrats Theory of conduct $ale of the Century Ayyavazhi mythology Yu-Gi-Oh! anime, manga or movie only characters Charmed Joke Social rule Infantilism Professional wrestling match types AFI 100 Years series Diaper Norway national football team Arianne New York Giants Sin City Jon Secada Urinary incontinence Alois Hitler Phoebe Buffay's songs Neopets Betting (poker) Satchel Paige San Francisco 49ers The Apprentice 2 Pittsburgh Steelers Eddie Guerrero Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Sharon Tate Slow Train Coming Draw poker Pregnancy Shaggy dog story Mario Babe Carey Scrabble Keno Ty Cobb Jeopardy! Luke and Laura Spencer Friends Baby Blues Kodocha Melanie Wilkes 1957 World Series Elephant Dick and Dom in